<html><head><title>The baby trap</title></head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<table width=100%><tr><td valign=top><img src="../images/br.gif" width=111 height=24  alt="Britain">
<p><font size=-1>
These articles in the Britain section are published in the UK printed edition only, and are published here for the benefit of readers of non-UK editions.
</font></p></td><td></td>
<td align=right valign=top><img src="http://www.economist.com/econlogosmall.gif" width=78 height=39  alt="The Economist">
</td></tr></table>
<table border=6><tr><td>



<h1>The baby trap</h1>
<p>AT THE centre of the debate about poverty, the underclass and all that is the single mother. If single mothers were not so poor, the cycle of deprivation would be broken.
<br>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;But single motherhood has very different consequences for a woman's prospects in different countries. A Joseph Rowntree Foundation companion study to the one above shows that single mothers in Britain have a lower chance of getting into employment, and thus out of poverty, than do those in most of the rest of the developed world (see <a href="br1.gif"> chart</a>).
<br>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;The disincentive to working does not lie in low pay, nor in the tax system. The after-tax income of a British single working mother is relatively high compared with other countries. Net disposable income for a single mother on income support is 65% of the same woman on half average earnings. In other words, she is quite a bit better off working.
<br>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;If it were not for the cost of childcare, that is. Many other developed countries' governments provide childcare, or assistance with it, allowing single mothers to work. Not so Britain, where the cost of childcare greatly adds to the cost of working. Once the income-replacement figure is adjusted to include the cost of childcare, it rises to 178%, so a single mother is a great deal better off staying at home than working. In France, where childcare is free, the figure is 71%.



</td></tr></table>
<br><p align=center><a href="http://www.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a> &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/cgi-bin/search_form.cgi?833583600,iss">Search</a>
 &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="index.html">Contents</a>
